# expgov

## Source of truth
- **Local-only WIP:** `maintainer/temp/` — temporary plans and scratch (**gitignored**).
- **Sprint / sequencing:** `maintainer/phases/active-phase.md`, `maintainer/phases/commands.md`.
- **Shipped receipts:** `maintainer/shipped/README.md` (check before re-implementing).
- **Engineering maps:** `maintainer/systems/README.md` (tiers, exports, config, cli, cache, principles).
- **Agent guides:** `maintainer/agents/README.md` · **Architecture:** `maintainer/agents/architecture.md` · **Rules:** `maintainer/agents/rules.md` · **Onboarding:** `maintainer/agents/onboarding.md`.

## Build / test gate
- Required before commit: `pnpm build` and `expgov validate` (dogfood root `expgov.config.ts`).
- Typecheck: `pnpm typecheck`.

## Config
- **TypeScript only:** `expgov.config.ts` via jiti — no JSON config.
- Tier schema: nested `tiers.{stable,internal,advanced}.{exact,prefix}` — see `maintainer/systems/tiers.md`.

## Core purity
- No `console.*` in `packages/core` command paths — use `emitLog`.
- Core never imports CLI or `@inquirer/prompts`.
- Chalk only in `runtime/style.ts` for semantic tokens.

## Source layout
- Types/interfaces → `packages/*/src/types/` (subdir barrels OK); logic files import, do not define or re-export them.
- Named constants → `packages/core/src/shared/constants/` or `packages/cli/src/constants/`.
- File-private `type` aliases (no export) are OK.
- Public SDK re-exports only from `packages/core/src/index.ts`.
- Details: `maintainer/agents/architecture.md` (Module organization).

## Export governance
- Root barrel: `packages/core/src/index.ts` (stable). Also `./advanced` and `./internal`.
- Classify exports via `@sdkTier` JSDoc or tier config buckets; do not put advanced/internal flats on root.
- Keep `package.json` exports, `expgov.config.ts` `core.subpaths`, and tsconfig paths aligned.
- Run `expgov validate` after changing public exports or tiers.

## CLI output
- Global flags: `-j/--json`, `-q/--quiet`, `-s/--silent`, `--no-color`.
- Help `(default: …)` uses bright yellow; rest dim.
- Per-command banners (off under `--json` / `--silent`).

## Docs boundary
- **`maintainer/**`** is contributor-only.
- **`docs/**`** is public copy (planned).

## v1 contract
- User-facing surfaces (CLI argv, `--json` envelope, exit codes) are semver-stable — breaking changes need a major bump.
- `@expgov/core` may grow additively in minor releases.
